      "subtopic": "camouflage",
      "passage": "Many small animals stay safe by blending into their surroundings. Cuttlefish change their skin color in less than a second to match nearby sand or rocks. Some lizards turn pale on bright surfaces and darker on shaded ground. This quick shift helps them avoid hungry birds that watch from above. Camouflage works best when an animal stays still after changing color.",
